reviews.review_text: tennis court show this is a great show,lot of energy.i was there for this show.i watched jerry arrive in his limo with his huge smile on his face as they drove through the crowd to the court.that made my day.when the concert started which of course was sold out,the crowd crashed the chain link fence around the court but that was not a problem. the 2nd set really rocked.i enjoyed this aud.great sound.i rate this show an overall"4".enjoy.

Tennis Anyone? This show was the best thing to come out of Indy since "One Day at a Time".  Features a killer Deal and awesome second set--even ol' Day Job didn't sound so bad...  Damn, I miss Summer Tour :)
My first Dead show! I was very happy to find this. This was my first time seeing the dead. I didn't really know much about them except for Truckin'.
